01/05/2006
KURDJALI, Bulgaria -- Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul praised the peaceful co-existence between Orthodox Christians and Muslims in the Bulgarian town of Kurdjali, where he paid an informal weekend visit. Gul visited the region, home to a large ethnic Turkish population, after attending an informal meeting of NATO foreign ministers in Sofia. In Kurdjali, he met with leaders of the Movement for Rights and Freedoms, a junior partner in Bulgaria's coalition government. (Focus - 01/05/06; Monitor - 30/04/06)
